HEADWORD: Locution
<hw>Lo*cu"tion</hw> <pr>(l⟦osl⟧*k⟦umac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>locutio</ets>, fr. <ets>loqui</ets> to speak: cf. F.
<ets>locution</ets>. ]</ety> <def>Speech or discourse; a phrase; a form
or mode of expression.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧ Stumbling
<xex>locutions</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I hate these figures in <qex>locution</qex>,⟦br⟧
